description: This room comes alive with your entrance.  Paintings with subtle
shades of gray squirm and contort in your presence, the faces within
them seeming to silently scream at you.  The floor writhes, pulling
softly at your leg, and then slipping away...  The horde of maggots
leaving you in peace.  All around you, the air is thick, pungent, with
a faint odor of mildew that makes it difficult to breathe.  Inhaling a
small fly on accident, you feel it slide slowly down your throat as
you peer about for exits.  There are none.  This is your fate.
Confess, and perhaps the Poison Maiden will be merciful.
